column5: Me, I just took a cab home!
Ya, saw that at the 1800 news last night, effective advertising, but there's always the idiots that can't follow the hints.
Wheres Cam Woolley, someones has his amazing sense of humour
He's too busy spouting his legal "opinions" on Canada's Worst Driver
love it , going to share it with guys at our detachment

I really cant believe people still drink and drive??? what the hell? Has anyone in the city tried UBER? We did on NYE and it was awesome until the way home (our own fault). After a few drinks, we clicked the wrong button and got a "black car". It was a nice ride but a $35 ride turned into and $80 ride in the fancier car...The original car was from UberX and was a spotless Volkswagen sedan. I feel sorry for the cab drivers,this service is just far too good. You can even track the car as it is enroute to you and read reviews on the driver etc...
